# Yubico FIDO attestation INTERMEDIATE CAs — not trust anchors.
#
# Modern YubiKeys (firmware 5.7+) do not sign the device attestation certificate
# directly with a root. The chain is:
#
#   device leaf
#     -> Yubico FIDO Attestation A/B/B2 1
#       -> Yubico Attestation Intermediate A/B 1
#         -> Yubico Attestation Root 1   (a trust anchor in yubico_fido_roots.pem)
#
# The attestation's x5c often carries only the leaf (and sometimes its immediate
# issuer), not the whole chain up to the root, so these intermediates are bundled
# to bridge the gap. They are loaded into the verifier's INTERMEDIATE pool, never
# as roots: trust is still anchored only at the roots file. Only the FIDO
# intermediates are included; the PIV/OpenPGP/SD/YubiHSM ones are irrelevant.
#
# Source: https://developers.yubico.com/PKI/yubico-intermediate.pem

